{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":165110,"duration_api_ms":164489,"num_turns":30,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"912c0549-b8c2-4afa-9ebd-9b6671add429","total_cost_usd":0.8708324999999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":21,"cache_creation_input_tokens":44738,"cache_read_input_tokens":846330,"output_tokens":6718,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":44738,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":21,"outputTokens":6718,"cacheReadInputTokens":846330,"cacheCreationInputTokens":44738,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.8708324999999999,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Reviewed the diff across `retry_policy.rs` and `engine.rs`. The changes cover: (1) increased retry limits (Transport 3→5, Schema 2→3, Timeout 2→3, BinaryNotFound terminal), (2) mandatory snapshot write during backoff replacing best-effort, (3) terminal failure clearing retry tracking in `derive_resume_state`, (4) cycle-advance pruning stale retry history, and (5) improved jitter hash mixing. All existing and new tests pass. The logic is correct — terminal failure clearing is sound (`.remove()` causes `.unwrap_or(1)` to reset attempt to 1 on resume), the `retain` cleanup on CycleAdvanced correctly uses `>= current_cycle`, and the jitter mixer distributes values adequately for its purpose. The behavioral change from best-effort to mandatory snapshot write (`?` propagation) is well-reasoned per the journal/snapshot divergence argument, and resume from journal replay would still work correctly even if the write fails mid-run. One amendment proposed for test coverage of the new failure path.","amendments":[{"body":"Add a test for the snapshot-write-failure-during-backoff path in the engine retry loop. The change at engine.rs:4649 converted `write_run_snapshot` from best-effort (log+swallow) to mandatory (`?` propagation), which is a behavioral change: a transient disk error during backoff now aborts the entire run instead of continuing. The project already has a `FailingSnapshotWrite` test fixture (conformance_spec/scenarios.rs:17922). A targeted test should inject a snapshot write failure during a retry-backoff window and verify that: (a) the engine returns an error rather than silently continuing, and (b) a subsequent `derive_resume_state` from the journal alone correctly reconstructs the retry position, confirming the journal is authoritative even when the snapshot is stale.","rationale":"This is the only new error-propagation path introduced by the diff that lacks dedicated test coverage. The behavioral change is correct but subtle — if a snapshot write fails, the run exits with an error, and correctness depends on journal-based resume working without a fresh snapshot. Testing this path prevents regressions and validates the invariant stated in the comment."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"0b0bfd63-aef6-4e64-9e98-782aac83d8ee"}
